sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K611074
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the test construct of BBa_K610097 used for pinpointing the location of promoter activity in the LVA-TAATAA-Barcode region of BBa_C0051. This construct contains the Barcode truncation where the last 8 bases on the 3' end have been truncated.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Timothy Fenton

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J61002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Plasmid for construction of promoter basic parts. Insertion of a promoter element between XbaI and SpeI sites results in a RFP reporter while retaining the ability to do biobrick assembly. Part J61002 is the tet promoter variant of the plasmid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Anderson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K611097
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: LVA Tag, Double Stop Codon, Truncated Barcode (3' -8bp)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a truncated version of the LVA Degradation Tag-TAATAA Double Stop Codon-Barcode region. The last 8 3' bases have been truncated from the Barcode in order to pinpoint where promoter activity is originating from in the LVA-TAATAA-Barcode region. This is part of 8 truncation combinations of this region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Timothy Fenton
